Hilary Mantel has revised the theatrical adaptation of her second novel Bring Up the Bodies for a run on Broadway . 
  The title has been changed to 'Wolf Hall II' and she has cut 'a lot of repetition' The British cast of the stage version opens tomorrow at the Winter Garden Theatre in Times Square . 
  The author said she believes the Broadway version of her books will be a hit . 
  The book was recently adapted for the BBC for a television series . 
 